formNotSupportedException>."},{"content":"The .NET Framework 4.7.2 now provides an implementation for these properties.","pos":[16472,16549]},{"content":"The properties are:","pos":[16550,16569]},{"pos":[16728,16737],"content":"SQLClient","linkify":"SQLClient","nodes":[{"content":"SQLClient","pos":[0,9]}]},{"pos":[16739,16834],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Support for Azure Active Directory Universal Authentication and Multi-Factor authentication<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**Support for Azure Active Directory Universal Authentication and Multi-Factor authentication**"},{"content":"Growing compliance and security demands require that many customers use multi-factor authentication (MFA).","pos":[16836,16942]},{"content":"In addition, current best practices discourage including user passwords directly in connection strings.","pos":[16943,17046]},{"content":"To support these changes, the .NET Framework 4.7.2 extends <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>SQLClient connection strings<ept id=\"p1\">](xref:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlConnection.ConnectionString)</ept> by adding a new value, \"Active Directory Interactive\", for the existing \"Authentication\" keyword to support MFA and <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>Azure AD Authentication<ept id=\"p2\">](/azure/sql-database/sql-database-aad-authentication-configure)</ept>.","pos":[17047,17401],"source":" To support these changes, the .NET Framework 4.7.2 extends [SQLClient connection strings](xref:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlConnection.ConnectionString) by adding a new value, \"Active Directory Interactive\", for the existing \"Authentication\" keyword to support MFA and [Azure AD Authentication](/azure/sql-database/sql-database-aad-authentication-configure)."},{"content":"The new interactive method supports native and federated Azure AD users as well as Azure AD guest users.","pos":[17402,17506]},{"content":"When this method is used, the MFA authentication imposed by Azure AD is supported for SQL databases.","pos":[17507,17607]},{"content":"In addition, the authentication process requests a user password to adhere to security best practices.","pos":[17608,17710]},{"content":"In previous versions of the .NET Framework, SQL connectivity supported only the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlAuthenticationMethod.ActiveDirectoryPassword?displayProperty=nameWithType&gt;</ph> and <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlAuthenticationMethod.ActiveDirectoryIntegrated?displayProperty=nameWithType&gt;</ph> options.","pos":[17712,18018],"source":"In previous versions of the .NET Framework, SQL connectivity supported only the <xref:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlAuthenticationMethod.ActiveDirectoryPassword?displayProperty=nameWithType> and <xref:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlAuthenticationMethod.ActiveDirectoryIntegrated?displayProperty=nameWithType> options."},{"content":"Both of these are part of the non-interactive <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>ADAL protocol<ept id=\"p1\">](/azure/active-directory/develop/active-directory-authentication-libraries)</ept>, which does not support MFA.","pos":[18019,18184],"source":" Both of these are part of the non-interactive [ADAL protocol](/azure/active-directory/develop/active-directory-authentication-libraries), which does not support MFA."},{"content":"With the new <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlAuthenticationMethod.ActiveDirectoryInteractive?displayProperty=nameWithType&gt;</ph> option, SQL connectivity supports MFA as well as existing authentication methods (password and integrated authentication), which allows users to enter user passwords interactively without persisting passwords in the connection string.","pos":[18185,18541],"source":" With the new <xref:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlAuthenticationMethod.ActiveDirectoryInteractive?displayProperty=nameWithType> option, SQL connectivity supports MFA as well as existing authentication methods (password and integrated authentication), which allows users to enter user passwords interactively without persist