der the [!INCLUDE[net_v462](../../../includes/net-v462-md.md)], you can disable per-monitor DPI changes in WPF apps by adding a configuration statement to the [\\<runtime>](../configure-apps/file-schema/runtime/runtime-element.md) section of your application configuration file, as follows:"},{"pos":[74526,74558],"content":"Windows Workflow Foundation (WF)","linkify":"Windows Workflow Foundation (WF)","nodes":[{"content":"Windows Workflow Foundation (WF)","pos":[0,32]}]},{"pos":[74560,74691],"content":"In the <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[net_v462](../../../includes/net-v462-md.md)]</ph>, Windows Workflow Foundation has been enhanced in the following area:","source":"In the [!INCLUDE[net_v462](../../../includes/net-v462-md.md)], Windows Workflow Foundation has been enhanced in the following area:"},{"pos":[74693,74769],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Support for C# expressions and IntelliSense in the Re-hosted WF Designer<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**Support for C# expressions and IntelliSense in the Re-hosted WF Designer**"},{"content":"Starting with the <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[net_v45](../../../includes/net-v45-md.md)]</ph>, WF supports C# expressions in both the Visual Studio Designer and in code workflows.","pos":[74771,74927],"source":"Starting with the [!INCLUDE[net_v45](../../../includes/net-v45-md.md)], WF supports C# expressions in both the Visual Studio Designer and in code workflows."},{"content":"The Re-hosted Workflow Designer is a key feature of WF that allows for the Workflow Designer to be in an application outside Visual Studio (for example, in WPF).","pos":[74928,75089]},{"content":"Windows Workflow Foundation provides the ability to support C# expressions and IntelliSense in the Re-hosted Workflow Designer.","pos":[75091,75218]},{"content":"For more information, see the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Windows Workflow Foundation blog<ept id=\"p1\">](https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkID=809042&amp;clcid=0x409)</ept>.","pos":[75219,75344],"source":" For more information, see the [Windows Workflow Foundation blog](https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkID=809042&clcid=0x409)."},{"content":"<ph id=\"ph1\">`Availability of IntelliSense when a customer rebuilds a workflow project from Visual Studio`</ph> In versions of the .NET Framework prior to the <ph id=\"ph2\">[!INCLUDE[net_v462](../../../includes/net-v462-md.md)]</ph>, WF Designer IntelliSense is broken when a customer rebuilds a workflow project from Visual Studio.","pos":[75346,75641],"source":"`Availability of IntelliSense when a customer rebuilds a workflow project from Visual Studio`\nIn versions of the .NET Framework prior to the [!INCLUDE[net_v462](../../../includes/net-v462-md.md)], WF Designer IntelliSense is broken when a customer rebuilds a workflow project from Visual Studio."},{"content":"While the project build is successful, the workflow types are not found on the designer, and warnings from IntelliSense for the missing workflow types appear in the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Error List<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> window.","pos":[75642,75829],"source":" While the project build is successful, the workflow types are not found on the designer, and warnings from IntelliSense for the missing workflow types appear in the **Error List** window."},{"content":"The <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[net_v462](../../../includes/net-v462-md.md)]</ph> addresses this issue and makes IntelliSense available.","pos":[75830,75943],"source":" The [!INCLUDE[net_v462](../../../includes/net-v462-md.md)] addresses this issue and makes IntelliSense available."},{"pos":[75945,76023],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Workflow V1 applications with Workflow Tracking on now run under FIPS-mode<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**Workflow V1 applications with Workflow Tracking on now run under FIPS-mode**"},{"content":"Machines with FIPS Compliance Mode enabled can now successfully run a workflow Version 1-style application with Workflow tracking on.","pos":[76025,76158]},{"content":"To enable this scenario, you must make the following change to your app.config file:","pos":[76159,76243]},{"content":"If this scenario is not enabled, running the application continues to generate an exception with the message, \"This implementation is not part of the Windows Platform FIPS validated cryptographic algorithms.\"","pos":[76323,76531]},{"pos":[76533,76621],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Workflow Improvements when using Dynamic Update with Visual Studio Workflow Designer<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**Workflow Improvements when using Dynamic Update with Visual Studio Workflow Designer**"},{"content":"The Workflow Designer, FlowChart Activity Designer, and other Workflow Activity Designers now successfully load and display workflows that have been saved after calling  the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Activities.DynamicUpdate.DynamicUpdateServices.PrepareForUpdate%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType&gt;</ph> method.","pos":[76623,76914],"source":"The Workflow Designer, FlowChart Activity Designer, and other Workflow Activity Designers now successfully load and display workflows that have been saved after calling  the <xref:System.Activities.DynamicUpdate.DynamicUpdateServices.PrepareForUpdate%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> method."},{"content":"In versions of the .NET Framework before the <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[net_v462](../../../includes/net-v462-md.md)]</ph>, loading a XAML file in Visual Studio for a workflow that has been saved after calling <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.Activities.DynamicUpdate.DynamicUpdateServices.PrepareForUpdate%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType&gt;</ph> can result in the following issues:","pos":[76915,77247],"source":" In versions of the .NET Framework before the [!INCLUDE[net_v462](../../../includes/net-v462-md.md)], loading a XAML file in Visual Studio for a workflow that has been saved after calling <xref:System.Activities.DynamicUpdate.DynamicUpdateServices.PrepareForUpdate%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> can result in the following issues:"},{"pos":[77251,77442],"content":"The Workflow Designer can't load the XAML file correctly (when the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Activities.Presentation.ViewState.ViewStateData.Id%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType&gt;</ph> is at the end of the line).","source":"The Workflow Designer can't load the XAML file correctly (when the <xref:System.Activities.Presentation.ViewState.ViewStateData.Id%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> is at the end of the line)."},{"content":"Flowchart Activity Designer or other Workflow Activity Designers may display all objects in their default locations as opposed to attached property values.","pos":[77446,77601]},{"pos":[77633,77642],"content":"ClickOnce","linkify":"ClickOnce","nodes":[{"content":"ClickOnce","pos":[0,9]}]},{"content":"ClickOnce has been updated to support TLS 1.1 and TLS 1.2 in addition to the 1.0 protocol, which it already supports.","pos":[77644,77761]},{"content":"ClickOnce automatically detects which protocol is required; no extra steps within the ClickOnce application are required to enable TLS 1.1 and 1.2 support.","pos":[77762,77917]},{"pos":[77948,77998],"content":"Converting Windows Forms and WPF apps to  UWP apps","linkify":"Converting Windows Forms and WPF apps to  UWP apps","nodes":[{"content":"Converting Windows Forms and WPF apps to  UWP apps","pos":[0,50]}]},{"content":"Windows now offers capabilities to bring existing Windows desktop apps, including WPF and Windows Forms apps, to the Universal Windows Platform (UWP).","pos":[78000,78150]},{"content":"This technology acts as a bridge by enabling you to gradually migrate your existing code base to UWP, thereby bringing your app to all Windows 10 devices.","pos":[78151,78305]},{"content":"Converted desktop apps gain an app identity similar to the app identity of UWP apps, which makes UWP APIs accessible to enable features such as Live Tiles and notifications.","pos":[78307,78480]},{"content":"The app continues to behave as before and runs as a full trust app.","pos":[78481,78548]},{"content":"Once the app is converted, an app container process can be added to the existing full trust process to add an adaptive user interface.","pos":[78549,78683]},{"content":"When all functionality is moved to the app container process, the full trust process can be removed and the new UWP app can be made available to all Windows 10 devices.","pos":[78684,78852]},{"pos":[78881,78903],"content":"Debugging improvements","linkify":"Debugging improvements","nodes":[{"content":"Debugging improvements","pos":[0,22]}]},{"content":"The <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>unmanaged debugging API<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> has been enhanced in the <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[net_v462](../../../includes/net-v462-md.md)]</ph> to perform additional analysis when a <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.NullReferenceException&gt;</ph> is thrown so that it is possible to determine which variable in a single line of source code is <ph id=\"ph3\">`null`</ph>.","pos":[78905,79193],"source":"The *unmanaged debugging API* has been enhanced in the [!INCLUDE[net_v462](../../../includes/net-v462-md.md)] to perform additional analysis when a <xref:System.NullReferenceException> is thrown so that it is possible to determine which variable in a single line of source code is `null`."},{"content":"To support this scenario, the following APIs have been added to the unmanaged debugging API.","pos":[79196,79288]},{"content":"The <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>ICorDebugCode4<ept id=\"p1\">](../unmanaged-api/debugging/icordebugcode4-interface.md)</ept>, <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>ICorDebugVariableHome<ept id=\"p2\">](../unmanaged-api/debugging/icordebugvariablehome-interface.md)</ept>, and <bpt id=\"p3\">[</bpt>ICorDebugVariableHomeEnum<ept id=\"p3\">](../unmanaged-api/debugging/icordebugvariablehomeenum-interface.md)</ept> interfaces, which expose the native homes of managed variables.","pos":[79292,79620],"source":"The [ICorDebugCode4](../unmanaged-api/debugging/icordebugcode4-interface.md), [ICorDebugVariableHome](../unmanaged-api/debugging/icordebugvariablehome-interface.md), and [ICorDebugVariableHomeEnum](../unmanaged-api/debugging/icordebugvariablehomeenum-interface.md) interfaces, which expose the native homes of managed variables."},{"content":"This enables debuggers to do some code flow analysis when a  <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.NullReferenceException&gt;</ph> occurs and to work backwards to determine the managed variable that corresponds to the native location that was <ph id=\"ph2\">`null`</ph>.","pos":[79621,79838],"source":" This enables debuggers to do some code flow analysis when a  <xref:System.NullReferenceException> occurs and to work backwards to determine the managed variable that corresponds to the native location that was `null`."},{"content":"The <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>ICorDebugType2::GetTypeID<ept id=\"p1\">](../unmanaged-api/debugging/icordebugtype2-gettypeid-method.md)</ept> method provides a mapping for ICorDebugType to <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>COR_TYPEID<ept id=\"p2\">](../unmanaged-api/debugging/cor-typeid-structure.md)</ept>, which allows the debugger to obtain a <bpt id=\"p3\">[</bpt>COR_TYPEID<ept id=\"p3\">](../unmanaged-api/debugging/cor-typeid-structure.md)</ept> without an instance of the ICorDebugType.","pos":[79842,80194],"source":"The [ICorDebugType2::GetTypeID](../unmanaged-api/debugging/icordebugtype2-gettypeid-method.md) method provides a mapping for ICorDebugType to [COR_TYPEID](../unmanaged-api/debugging/cor-typeid-structure.md), which allows the debugger to obtain a [COR_TYPEID](../unmanaged-api/debugging/cor-typeid-structure.md) without an instance of the ICorDebugType."},{"content":"Existing APIs on <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>COR_TYPEID<ept id=\"p1\">](../unmanaged-api/debugging/cor-typeid-structure.md)</ept> can then be used to determine the class layout of the type.","pos":[80195,80336],"source":" Existing APIs on [COR_TYPEID](../unmanaged-api/debugging/cor-typeid-structure.md) can then be used to determine the class layout of the type."},{"pos":[80360,80398],"content":"What's new in the .NET Framework 4.6.1","linkify":"What's new in the .NET Framework 4.6.1","nodes":[{"content":"What's new in the .NET Framework 4.6.1","pos":[0,38]}]},{"pos":[80400,80504],"content":"The <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[net_v461](../../../includes/net-v461-md.md)]</ph> includes new features in the following areas:","source":"The [!INCLUDE[net_v461](../../../includes/net-v461-md.md)] includes new features in the following areas:"},{"pos":[80508,80531],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Cryptography<ept id=\"p1\">](#Crypto)</ept>","source":"[Cryptography](#Crypto)"},{"pos":[80535,80557],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>ADO.NET<ept id=\"p1\">](#ADO.NET461)</ept>","source":"[ADO.NET](#ADO.NET461)"},{"pos":[80561,80609],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Windows Presentation Foundation (WPF)<ept id=\"p1\">](#WPF461)</ept>","source":"[Windows Presentation Foundation (WPF)](#WPF461)"},{"pos":[80613,80651],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Windows Workflow Foundation<ept id=\"p1\">](#WWF461)</ept>","source":"[Windows Workflow Foundation](#WWF461)"},{"pos":[80655,80679],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Profiling<ept id=\"p1\">](#Profile461)</ept>","source":"[Profiling](#Profile461)"},{"pos":[80683,80699],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>NGen<ept id=\"p1\">](#NGEN461)</ept>","source":"[NGen](#NGEN461)"},{"pos":[80701,80810],"content":"For more information on the <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[net_v461](../../../includes/net-v461-md.md)]</ph>, see the following topics:","source":"For more information on the [!INCLUDE[net_v461](../../../includes/net-v461-md.md)], see the following topics:"},{"pos":[80814,80904],"content":"The <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>.NET Framework 4.6.1 list of changes<ept id=\"p1\">](https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=622964)</ept>","source":"The [.NET Framework 4.6.1 list of changes](https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=622964)"},{"pos":[80908,81020],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Application Compatibility in 4.6.1<ept id=\"p1\">](../migration-guide/application-compatibility-in-the-net-framework-4-6-1.md)</ept>","source":"[Application Compatibility in 4.6.1](../migration-guide/application-compatibility-in-the-net-framework-4-6-1.md)"},{"pos":[81024,81113],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>The .NET Framework API diff<ept id=\"p1\">](https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=622989)</ept> (on GitHub)","source":"[The .NET Framework API diff](https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=622989) (on GitHub)"},{"pos":[81140,81200],"content":"Cryptography: Support for X509 certificates containing ECDSA","linkify":"Cryptography: Support for X509 certificates containing ECDSA","nodes":[{"content":"Cryptography: Support for X509 certificates containing ECDSA","pos":[0,60]}]},{"content":"The .NET Framework 4.6 added RSACng support for X509 certificates.","pos":[81202,81268]},{"content":"The <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[net_v461](../../../includes/net-v461-md.md)]</ph> adds support for ECDSA (Elliptic Curve Digital Signature Algorithm) X509 certificates.","pos":[81269,81414],"source":" The [!INCLUDE[net_v461](../../../includes/net-v461-md.md)] adds support for ECDSA (Elliptic Curve Digital Signature Algorithm) X509 certificates."},{"content":"ECDSA offers better performance and is a more secure cryptography algorithm than RSA, providing an excellent choice where Transport Layer Security (TLS) performance and scalability is a concern.","pos":[81416,81610]},{"content":"The .NET Framework implementation wraps calls into existing Windows functionality.","pos":[81611,81693]},{"pos":[81695,81911],"content":"The following example code shows how easy it is to generate a signature for a byte stream by using the new  support for ECDSA  X509 certificates included in the <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[net_v461](../../../includes/net-v461-md.md)]</ph>.","source":"The following example code shows how easy it is to generate a signature for a byte stream by using the new  support for ECDSA  X509 certificates included in the [!INCLUDE[net_v461](../../../includes/net-v461-md.md)]."},{"content":"This offers a marked contrast to the code needed to generate a signature in the .NET Framework 4.6.","pos":[82148,82247]},{"pos":[82512,82519],"content":"ADO.NET","linkify":"ADO.NET","nodes":[{"content":"ADO.NET","pos":[0,7]}]},{"content":"The following have been added to ADO.NET:","pos":[82521,82562]},{"pos":[82564,82620],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Always Encrypted support for hardware protected keys<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**Always Encrypted support for hardware protected keys**"},{"content":"ADO.NET now supports storing Always Encrypted column master keys natively in Hardware Security Modules (HSMs).","pos":[82622,82732]},{"content":"With this support, customers can leverage asymmetric keys stored in HSMs without having to write custom column master key store providers and registering them in applications.","pos":[82733,82908]},{"content":"Customers need to install the HSM vendor-provided CSP provider or CNG key store providers on the app servers or client computers in order to access Always Encrypted data protected with column master keys stored in a HSM.","pos":[82910,83130]},{"pos":[83132,83256],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Improved <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlConnectionStringBuilder.MultiSubnetFailover%2A&gt;</ph> connection behavior for AlwaysOn<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**Improved <xref:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlConnectionStringBuilder.MultiSubnetFailover%2A> connection behavior for AlwaysOn**"},{"content":"SqlClient now automatically provides faster connections to an AlwaysOn Availability Group (AG).","pos":[83258,83353]},{"content":"It transparently detects whether your application is connecting to an AlwaysOn availability group (AG) on a different subnet and quickly discovers the current active server and provides a connection to the server.","pos":[83354,83567]},{"content":"Prior to this release, an application had to set the connection string to include <ph id=\"ph1\">`\"MultisubnetFailover=true\"`</ph> to indicate that it was connecting to an AlwaysOn Availability Group.","pos":[83568,83748],"source":" Prior to this release, an application had to set the connection string to include `\"MultisubnetFailover=true\"` to indicate that it was connecting to an AlwaysOn Availability Group."},{"content":"Without setting the connection keyword to <ph id=\"ph1\">`true`</ph>, an application might experience a timeout while connecting to an AlwaysOn Availability Group.","pos":[83749,83892],"source":" Without setting the connection keyword to `true`, an application might experience a timeout while connecting to an AlwaysOn Availability Group."},{"content":"With this release, an application does <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>not<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> need to set <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlConnectionStringBuilder.MultiSubnetFailover%2A&gt;</ph> to <ph id=\"ph2\">`true`</ph> anymore.","pos":[83893,84047],"source":" With this release, an application does *not* need to set <xref:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlConnectionStringBuilder.MultiSubnetFailover%2A> to `true` anymore."},{"content":"For more information about SqlClient support for Always On Availability Groups, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>SqlClient Support for High Availability, Disaster Recovery<ept id=\"p1\">](../data/adonet/sql/sqlclient-support-for-high-availability-disaster-recovery.md)</ept>.","pos":[84048,84274],"source":" For more information about SqlClient support for Always On Availability Groups, see [SqlClient Support for High Availability, Disaster Recovery](../data/adonet/sql/sqlclient-support-for-high-availability-disaster-recovery.md)."},{"pos":[84301,84338],"content":"Windows Presentation Foundation (WPF)","linkify":"Windows Presentation Foundation (WPF)","nodes":[{"content":"Windows Presentation Foundation (WPF)","pos":[0,37]}]},{"content":"Windows Presentation Foundation includes a number of improvements and changes.","pos":[84340,84418]},{"pos":[84420,84444],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Improved performance<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**Improved performance**"},{"content":"The delay in firing touch events has been fixed in the <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[net_v461](../../../includes/net-v461-md.md)]</ph>.","pos":[84446,84556],"source":"The delay in firing touch events has been fixed in the [!INCLUDE[net_v461](../../../includes/net-v461-md.md)]."},{"content":"In addition, typing in a <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.RichTextBox&gt;</ph> control no longer ties up the render thread during fast input.","pos":[84557,84687],"source":" In addition, typing in a <xref:System.Windows.Controls.RichTextBox> control no longer ties up the render thread during fast input."},{"pos":[84689,84720],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Spell checking improvements<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**Spell checking improvements**"},{"content":"The spell checker in WPF has been updated on Windows 8.1 and later versions to leverage operating system support for spell-checking additional languages.","pos":[84722,84875]},{"content":"There is no change in functionality on Windows versions prior to Windows 8.1.","pos":[84877,84954]},{"pos":[84956,85184],"content":"As in previous versions of the .NET Framework, the language for a <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.TextBox&gt;</ph> control ora <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.RichTextBox&gt;</ph> block is detected by looking for information in the following order:","source":"As in previous versions of the .NET Framework, the language for a <xref:System.Windows.Controls.TextBox> control ora <xref:System.Windows.Controls.RichTextBox> block is detected by looking for information in the following order:"},{"pos":[85188,85217],"content":"<ph id=\"ph1\">`xml:lang`</ph>, if it is present.","source":"`xml:lang`, if it is present."},{"content":"Current input language.","pos":[85221,85244]},{"content":"Current thread culture.","pos":[85248,85271]},{"pos":[85273,85433],"content":"For additional information on language support in WPF, see the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>WPF blog post on .NET Framework 4.6.1 features<ept id=\"p1\">](https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkID=691819)</ept>.","source":"For additional information on language support in WPF, see the [WPF blog post on .NET Framework 4.6.1 features](https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkID=691819)."},{"pos":[85435,85490],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Additional support for per-user custom dictionaries<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**Additional support for per-user custom dictionaries**"},{"content":"In <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[net_v461](../../../includes/net-v461-md.md)]</ph>, WPF recognizes custom dictionaries that are registered globally.","pos":[85492,85615],"source":"In [!INCLUDE[net_v461](../../../includes/net-v461-md.md)], WPF recognizes custom dictionaries that are registered globally."},{"content":"This capability is available in addition to the ability to register them per-control.","pos":[85616,85701]},{"content":"In previous versions of WPF, custom dictionaries did not recognize Excluded Words and AutoCorrect lists.","pos":[85703,85807]},{"content":"They are supported on Windows 8.1 and Windows 10 through the use of files that can be placed under the <ph id=\"ph1\">`%AppData%\\Microsoft\\Spelling\\&lt;language tag&gt;`</ph> directory.","pos":[85808,85967],"source":" They are supported on Windows 8.1 and Windows 10 through the use of files that can be placed under the `%AppData%\\Microsoft\\Spelling\\<language tag>` directory."},{"content":"The following rules apply to these files:","pos":[85969,86010]},{"content":"The files should have extensions of .dic (for added words), .exc (for excluded words), or .acl (for AutoCorrect).","pos":[86014,86127]},{"content":"The files should be UTF-16 LE plaintext that starts with the Byte Order Mark (BOM).","pos":[86131,86214]},{"content":"Each line should consist of a word (in the added and excluded word lists), or an autocorrect pair with the words separated by a vertical bar (\"&amp;#124;\") (in the AutoCorrect word list).","pos":[86218,86401],"source":"Each line should consist of a word (in the added and excluded word lists), or an autocorrect pair with the words separated by a vertical bar (\"&#124;\") (in the AutoCorrect word list)."},{"content":"These files are considered read-only and are not modified by the system.","pos":[86405,86477]},{"pos":[86481,86667],"content":"[!NOTE]\nThese new file-formats are not directly supported by the WPF spell checking APIs, and the custom dictionaries supplied to WPF in applications should continue to use .lex files.","leadings":["","> "],"nodes":[{"content":"These new file-formats are not directly supported by the WPF spell checking APIs, and the custom dictionaries supplied to WPF in applications should continue to use .lex files.","pos":[8,184]}]},{"pos":[86669,86680],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Samples<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**Samples**"},{"content":"There are a number of WPF samples on the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Microsoft/WPF-Samples<ept id=\"p1\">](https://github.com/Microsoft/WPF-Samples)</ept> GitHub repository.","pos":[86682,86807],"source":"There are a number of WPF samples on the [Microsoft/WPF-Samples](https://github.com/Microsoft/WPF-Samples) GitHub repository."},{"content":"Help us improve our samples by sending us a pull-request or opening a <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>GitHub issue<ept id=\"p1\">](https://github.com/Microsoft/WPF-Samples/issues)</ept>.","pos":[86808,86942],"source":" Help us improve our samples by sending us a pull-request or opening a [GitHub issue](https://github.com/Microsoft/WPF-Samples/issues)."},{"pos":[86944,86966],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>DirectX extensions<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**DirectX extensions**"},{"content":"WPF includes a <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>NuGet package<ept id=\"p1\">](https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkID=691342)</ept> that provides new implementations of <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Interop.D3DImage&gt;</ph> that make it easy for you to interoperate with DX10 and Dx11 content.","pos":[86968,87192],"source":"WPF includes a [NuGet package](https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkID=691342) that provides new implementations of <xref:System.Windows.Interop.D3DImage> that make it easy for you to interoperate with DX10 and Dx11 content."},{"content":"The code for this package has been open sourced and is available <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>on GitHub<ept id=\"p1\">](https://github.com/Microsoft/WPFDXInterop)</ept>.","pos":[87193,87313],"source":" The code for this package has been open sourced and is available [on GitHub](https://github.com/Microsoft/WPFDXInterop)."},{"pos":[87340,87381],"content":"Windows Workflow Foundation: Transactions","linkify":"Windows Workflow Foundation: Transactions","nodes":[{"content":"Windows Workflow Foundation: Transactions","pos":[0,41]}]},{"content":"The <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Transactions.Transaction.EnlistPromotableSinglePhase%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType&gt;</ph> method can now use a distributed transaction manager other than MSDTC to promote the transaction.","pos":[87383,87583],"source":"The <xref:System.Transactions.Transaction.EnlistPromotableSinglePhase%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> method can now use a distributed transaction manager other than MSDTC to promote the transaction."},{"content":"You do this by specifying a GUID transaction promoter identifier to the  new <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Transactions.Transaction.EnlistPromotableSinglePhase%28System.Transactions.IPromotableSinglePhaseNotification%2CSystem.Guid%29?displayProperty=nameWithType&gt;</ph> overload .","pos":[87584,87841],"source":" You do this by specifying a GUID transaction promoter identifier to the  new <xref:System.Transactions.Transaction.EnlistPromotableSinglePhase%28System.Transactions.IPromotableSinglePhaseNotification%2CSystem.Guid%29?displayProperty=nameWithType> overload ."},{"content":"If this operation is successful, there are limitations placed on the capabilities of the transaction.","pos":[87842,87943]},{"content":"Once a non-MSDTC transaction promoter is enlisted, the following methods throw a <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Transactions.TransactionPromotionException&gt;</ph> because these methods require promotion to MSDTC:","pos":[87944,88131],"source":" Once a non-MSDTC transaction promoter is enlisted, the following methods throw a <xref:System.Transactions.TransactionPromotionException> because these methods require promotion to MSDTC:"},{"content":"Once a non-MSDTC transaction promoter is enlisted, it must be used for future durable enlistments by using protocols that it defines.","pos":[88529,88662]},{"content":"The <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Guid&gt;</ph> of the transaction promoter can be obtained by using the <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.Transactions.Transaction.PromoterType%2A&gt;</ph> property.","pos":[88663,88807],"source":" The <xref:System.Guid> of the transaction promoter can be obtained by using the <xref:System.Transactions.Transaction.PromoterType%2A> property."},{"content":"When the transaction promotes, the transaction promoter provides a <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Byte&gt;</ph> array that represents the promoted token.","pos":[88808,88935],"source":" When the transaction promotes, the transaction promoter provides a <xref:System.Byte> array that represents the promoted token."},{"content":"An application can obtain the promoted token for a non-MSDTC promoted transaction with the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Transactions.Transaction.GetPromotedToken%2A&gt;</ph> method.","pos":[88936,89093],"source":" An application can obtain the promoted token for a non-MSDTC promoted transaction with the <xref:System.Transactions.Transaction.GetPromotedToken%2A> method."},{"content":"Users of the new <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Transactions.Transaction.EnlistPromotableSinglePhase%28System.Transactions.IPromotableSinglePhaseNotification%2CSystem.Guid%29?displayProperty=nameWithType&gt;</ph> overload must follow a specific call sequence in order for the promotion operation to complete successfully.","pos":[89095,89390],"source":"Users of the new <xref:System.Transactions.Transaction.EnlistPromotableSinglePhase%28System.Transactions.IPromotableSinglePhaseNotification%2CSystem.Guid%29?displayProperty=nameWithType> overload must follow a specific call sequence in order for the promotion operation to complete successfully."},{"content":"These rules are documented in the method's documentation.","pos":[89391,89448]},{"pos":[89479,89488],"content":"Profiling","linkify":"Profiling","nodes":[{"content":"Profiling","pos":[0,9]}]},{"content":"The unmanaged profiling API has been enhanced as follows:","pos":[89490,89547]},{"pos":[89551,89681],"content":"Better support for accessing PDBs in the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>ICorProfilerInfo7<ept id=\"p1\">](../unmanaged-api/profiling/icorprofilerinfo7-interface.md)</ept> interface.","source":"Better support for accessing PDBs in the [ICorProfilerInfo7](../unmanaged-api/profiling/icorprofilerinfo7-interface.md) interface."},{"content":"In ASP.NET Core, it is becoming much more common for assemblies to be compiled in-memory by Roslyn.","pos":[89686,89785]},{"content":"For developers making profiling tools, this means that PDBs that historically were serialized on disk may no longer be present.","pos":[89786,89913]},{"content":"Profiler tools often use PDBs to map code back to source lines for tasks such as code coverage or line-by-line performance analysis.","pos":[89914,90046]},{"content":"The <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>ICorProfilerInfo7<ept id=\"p1\">](../unmanaged-api/profiling/icorprofilerinfo7-interface.md)</ept> interface now includes two new methods, <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>ICorProfilerInfo7::GetInMemorySymbolsLength<ept id=\"p2\">](../unmanaged-api/profiling/icorprofilerinfo7-getinmemorysymbolslength-method.md)</ept> and <bpt id=\"p3\">[</bpt>ICorProfilerInfo7::ReadInMemorySymbols<ept id=\"p3\">](../unmanaged-api/profiling/icorprofilerinfo7-readinmemorysymbols.md)</ept>, to provide these profiler tools with access to the in-memory PDB data, By using the new APIs, a profiler can obtain the contents of an in-memory PDB as a byte array and then process it or serialize it to disk.","pos":[90047,90621],"source":" The [ICorProfilerInfo7](../unmanaged-api/profiling/icorprofilerinfo7-interface.md) interface now includes two new methods, [ICorProfilerInfo7::GetInMemorySymbolsLength](../unmanaged-api/profiling/icorprofilerinfo7-getinmemorysymbolslength-method.md) and [ICorProfilerInfo7::ReadInMemorySymbols](../unmanaged-api/profiling/icorprofilerinfo7-readinmemorysymbols.md), to provide these profiler tools with access to the in-memory PDB data, By using the new APIs, a profiler can obtain the contents of an in-memory PDB as a byte array and then process it or serialize it to disk."},{"content":"Better instrumentation with the ICorProfiler interface.","pos":[90625,90680]},{"content":"Profilers that are using the <ph id=\"ph1\">`ICorProfiler`</ph> APIs ReJit functionality for dynamic instrumentation can now modify some metadata.","pos":[90685,90811],"source":"Profilers that are using the `ICorProfiler` APIs ReJit functionality for dynamic instrumentation can now modify some metadata."},{"content":"Previously such tools could instrument IL at any time, but metadata could only be modified at module load time.","pos":[90812,90923]},{"content":"Because IL refers to metadata, this limited the kinds of instrumentation that could be done.","pos":[90924,91016]},{"content":"We have lifted some of those limits by adding the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>ICorProfilerInfo7::ApplyMetaData<ept id=\"p1\">](../unmanaged-api/profiling/icorprofilerinfo7-applymetadata-method.md)</ept> method to support a subset of metadata edits after the module loads, in particular by adding new <ph id=\"ph1\">`AssemblyRef`</ph>, <ph id=\"ph2\">`TypeRef`</ph>, <ph id=\"ph3\">`TypeSpec`</ph>, <ph id=\"ph4\">`MemberRef`</ph>, <ph id=\"ph5\">`MemberSpec`</ph>, and <ph id=\"ph6\">`UserString`</ph> records.","pos":[91017,91359],"source":" We have lifted some of those limits by adding the [ICorProfilerInfo7::ApplyMetaData](../unmanaged-api/profiling/icorprofilerinfo7-applymetadata-method.md) method to support a subset of metadata edits after the module loads, in particular by adding new `AssemblyRef`, `TypeRef`, `TypeSpec`, `MemberRef`, `MemberSpec`, and `UserString` records."},{"content":"This change makes a much broader range of on-the-fly instrumentation possible.","pos":[91360,91438]},{"pos":[91466,91500],"content":"Native Image Generator (NGEN) PDBs","linkify":"Native Image Generator (NGEN) PDBs","nodes":[{"content":"Native Image Generator (NGEN) PDBs","pos":[0,34]}]},{"content":"Cross-machine event tracing allows customers to profile a program on Machine A and look at the profiling data with source line mapping on Machine B. Using previous versions of the .NET Framework, the user would copy all the modules and native images from the profiled machine to the analysis machine that contains the IL PDB to create the source-to-native mapping.","pos":[91502,91866]},{"content":"While this process may work well when the files are relatively small, such as for phone applications, the files can be very large on desktop systems and require significant time to copy.","pos":[91867,92053]},{"content":"With Ngen PDBs, NGen can create a PDB that contains the IL-to-native mapping without a dependency on the IL PDB.","pos":[92055,92167]},{"content":"In our cross-machine event tracing scenario, all that is needed is to copy the native image PDB that is generated by Machine A to Machine B and to use <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Debug Interface Access APIs<ept id=\"p1\">](/visualstudio/debugger/debug-interface-access/debug-interface-access-sdk-reference)</ept> to read the IL PDB's source-to-IL mapping and the native image PDB's IL-to-native mapping.","pos":[92168,92523],"source":" In our cross-machine event tracing scenario, all that is needed is to copy the native image PDB that is generated by Machine A to Machine B and to use [Debug Interface Access APIs](/visualstudio/debugger/debug-interface-access/debug-interface-access-sdk-reference) to read the IL PDB's source-to-IL mapping and the native image PDB's IL-to-native mapping."},{"content":"Combining both mappings provides a source-to-native mapping.","pos":[92524,92584]},{"content":"Since the native image PDB is much smaller than all the modules and native images, the process of copying from Machine A to Machine B is much faster.","pos":[92585,92734]},{"pos":[92757,92780],"content":"What's new in .NET 2015","linkify":"What's new in .NET 2015","nodes":[{"content":"What's new in .NET 2015","pos":[0,23]}]},{"content":".NET 2015 introduces the <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[net_v46](../../../includes/net-v46-md.md)]</ph> and .NET Core.","pos":[92782,92874],"source":".NET 2015 introduces the [!INCLUDE[net_v46](../../../includes/net-v46-md.md)] and .NET Core."},{"content":"Some new features apply to both, and other features are specific to <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[net_v46](../../../includes/net-v46-md.md)]</ph> or <ph id=\"ph2\">[!INCLUDE[net_core](../../../includes/net-core-md.md)]</ph>.","pos":[92875,93054],"source":" Some new features apply to both, and other features are specific to [!INCLUDE[net_v46](../../../includes/net-v46-md.md)] or [!INCLUDE[net_core](../../../includes/net-core-md.md)]."},{"pos":[93058,93074],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>ASP.NET Core<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**ASP.NET Core**"},{"content":".NET 2015 includes ASP.NET Core, which is a lean .NET implementation for building modern cloud-based apps.","pos":[93081,93187]},{"content":"ASP.NET Core is modular so you can include only those features that are needed in your application.","pos":[93188,93287]},{"content":"It can be hosted on IIS or self-hosted in a custom process, and you can run apps with different versions of the .NET Framework on the same server.","pos":[93288,93434]},{"content":"It includes a new environment configuration system that is designed for cloud deployment.","pos":[93435,93524]},{"content":"MVC, Web API, and Web Pages are unified into a single framework called MVC 6.","pos":[93531,93608]},{"content":"You build ASP.NET Core apps through tools in Visual Studio 2015 or later.","pos":[93609,93682]},{"content":"Your existing applications will work on the new .NET Framework; however to build an app that uses MVC 6 or SignalR 3, you must use the project system in Visual Studio 2015 or later.","pos":[93683,93864]},{"pos":[93871,93922],"content":"For information, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>ASP.NET Core<ept id=\"p1\">](/aspnet/core/)</ept>.","source":"For information, see [ASP.NET Core](/aspnet/core/)."},{"pos":[93926,93945],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>ASP.NET Updates<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**ASP.NET Updates**"},{"pos":[93953,94006],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Task-based API for Asynchronous Response Flushing<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**Task-based API for Asynchronous Response Flushing**"},{"pos":[94017,94271],"content":"ASP.NET now provides a simple task-based API for asynchronous response flushing, <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Web.HttpResponse.FlushAsync%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType&gt;</ph>, that allows responses to be flushed asynchronously by using your language's <ph id=\"ph2\">`async/await`</ph> support.","source":"ASP.NET now provides a simple task-based API for asynchronous response flushing, <xref:System.Web.HttpResponse.FlushAsync%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType>, that allows responses to be flushed asynchronously by using your language's `async/await` support."},{"pos":[94279,94328],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Model binding supports task-returning methods<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**Model binding supports task-returning methods**"},{"content":"In the <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[net_v45](../../../includes/net-v45-md.md)]</ph>, ASP.NET added the Model Binding feature that enabled an extensible, code-focused approach to CRUD-based data operations in Web Forms pages and user controls.","pos":[94339,94557],"source":"In the [!INCLUDE[net_v45](../../../includes/net-v45-md.md)], ASP.NET added the Model Binding feature that enabled an extensible, code-focused approach to CRUD-based data operations in Web Forms pages and user controls."},{"content":"The Model Binding system now supports <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Threading.Tasks.Task&gt;</ph>-returning model binding methods.","pos":[94558,94663],"source":" The Model Binding system now supports <xref:System.Threading.Tasks.Task>-returning model binding methods."},{"content":"This feature allows Web Forms developers to get the scalability benefits of async with the ease of the data-binding system when using newer versions of ORMs, including the Entity Framework.","pos":[94664,94853]},{"pos":[94864,94960],"content":"Async model binding is controlled by the <ph id=\"ph1\">`aspnet:EnableAsyncModelBinding`</ph> configuration setting.","source":"Async model binding is controlled by the `aspnet:EnableAsyncModelBinding` configuration setting."},{"content":"On apps the target the <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[net_v46](../../../includes/net-v46-md.md)]</ph>, it defaults to <ph id=\"ph2\">`true`</ph>.","pos":[95120,95219],"source":"On apps the target the [!INCLUDE[net_v46](../../../includes/net-v46-md.md)], it defaults to `true`."},{"content":"On apps running on the <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[net_v46](../../../includes/net-v46-md.md)]</ph> that target an earlier version of the .NET Framework, it is <ph id=\"ph2\">`false`</ph> by default.","pos":[95220,95375],"source":" On apps running on the [!INCLUDE[net_v46](../../../includes/net-v46-md.md)] that target an earlier version of the .NET Framework, it is `false` by default."},{"content":"It can be enabled by setting the configuration setting to <ph id=\"ph1\">`true`</ph>.","pos":[95376,95441],"source":" It can be enabled by setting the configuration setting to `true`."},{"pos":[95449,95480],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>HTTP/2 Support (Windows 10)<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**HTTP/2 Support (Windows 10)**"},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>HTTP/2<ept id=\"p1\">](https://www.wikipedia.org/wiki/HTTP/2)</ept> is a new version of the HTTP protocol that provides much better connection utilization (fewer round-trips between client and server), resulting in lower latency web page loading for users.","pos":[95491,95727],"source":"[HTTP/2](https://www.wikipedia.org/wiki/HTTP/2) is a new version of the HTTP protocol that provides much better connection utilization (fewer round-trips between client and server), resulting in lower latency web page loading for users."},{"content":"Web pages (as opposed to services) benefit the most from HTTP/2, since the protocol optimizes for multiple artifacts being requested as part of a single experience.","pos":[95729,95893]},{"content":"HTTP/2 support has been added to ASP.NET in the .NET Framework 4.6.","pos":[95894,95961]},{"content":"Because networking functionality exists at multiple layers, new features were required in Windows, in IIS, and in ASP.NET to enable HTTP/2.","pos":[95962,96101]},{"content":"You must be running on Windows 10 to use HTTP/2 with ASP.NET.","pos":[96102,96163]},{"pos":[96174,96350],"content":"HTTP/2 is also supported and on by default for Windows 10 Universal Windows Platform (UWP) apps that use the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Net.Http.HttpClient?displayProperty=nameWithType&gt;</ph> API.","source":"HTTP/2 is also supported and on by default for Windows 10 Universal Windows Platform (UWP) apps that use the <xref:System.Net.Http.HttpClient?displayProperty=nameWithType> API."},{"pos":[96361,96786],"content":"In order to provide a way to use the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>PUSH_PROMISE<ept id=\"p1\">](https://http2.github.io/http2-spec/#PUSH_PROMISE)</ept> feature in ASP.NET applications, a new method with two overloads, <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Web.HttpResponse.PushPromise%28System.String%29&gt;</ph> and <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.Web.HttpResponse.PushPromise%28System.String%2CSystem.String%2CSystem.Collections.Specialized.NameValueCollection%29&gt;</ph>, has been added to the <ph id=\"ph3\">&lt;xref:System.Web.HttpResponse&gt;</ph> class.","source":"In order to provide a way to use the [PUSH_PROMISE](https://http2.github.io/http2-spec/#PUSH_PROMISE) feature in ASP.NET applications, a new method with two overloads, <xref:System.Web.HttpResponse.PushPromise%28System.String%29> and <xref:System.Web.HttpResponse.PushPromise%28System.String%2CSystem.String%2CSystem.Collections.Specialized.NameValueCollection%29>, has been added to the <xref:System.Web.HttpResponse> class."},{"pos":[96798,96912],"content":"[!NOTE]\nWhile ASP.NET Core supports HTTP/2, support for the PUSH PROMISE feature has not yet been added.","leadings":["","        > "],"nodes":[{"content":"While ASP.NET Core supports HTTP/2, support for the PUSH PROMISE feature has not yet been added.","pos":[8,104]}]},{"content":"The browser and the web server (IIS on Windows) do all the work.","pos":[96923,96987]},{"content":"You don't have to do any heavy-lifting for your users.","pos":[96988,97042]},{"pos":[97053,97228],"content":"Most of the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>major browsers support HTTP/2<ept id=\"p1\">](https://www.wikipedia.org/wiki/HTTP/2)</ept>, so it's likely that your users will benefit from HTTP/2 support if your server supports it.","source":"Most of the [major browsers support HTTP/2](https://www.wikipedia.org/wiki/HTTP/2), so it's likely that your users will benefit from HTTP/2 support if your server supports it."},{"pos":[97236,97278],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Support for the Token Binding Protocol<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**Support for the Token Binding Protocol**"},{"content":"Microsoft and Google have been collaborating on a new approach to authentication, called the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Token Binding Protocol<ept id=\"p1\">](https://github.com/TokenBinding/Internet-Drafts)</ept>.","pos":[97289,97456],"source":"Microsoft and Google have been collaborating on a new approach to authentication, called the [Token Binding Protocol](https://github.com/TokenBinding/Internet-Drafts)."},{"content":"The premise is that authentication tokens (in your browser cache) can be stolen and used by criminals to access otherwise secure resources (e.g. your bank account) without requiring your password or any other privileged knowledge.","pos":[97457,97687]},{"content":"The new protocol aims to mitigate this problem.","pos":[97688,97735]},{"content":"The Token Binding Protocol will be implemented in Windows 10 as a browser feature.","pos":[97746,97828]},{"content":"ASP.NET apps will participate in the protocol, so that authentication tokens are validated to be legitimate.","pos":[97829,97937]},{"content":"The client and the server implementations establish the end-to-end protection specified by the protocol.","pos":[97938,98042]},{"pos":[98050,98087],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Randomized string hash algorithms<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**Randomized string hash algorithms**"},{"content":"The .NET Framework 4.5 introduced a <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>randomized string hash algorithm<ept id=\"p1\">](../configure-apps/file-schema/runtime/userandomizedstringhashalgorithm-element.md)</ept>.","pos":[98098,98252],"source":"The .NET Framework 4.5 introduced a [randomized string hash algorithm](../configure-apps/file-schema/runtime/userandomizedstringhashalgorithm-element.md)."},{"content":"However, it was not supported by ASP.NET because of some ASP.NET features depended on a stable hash code.","pos":[98253,98358]},{"content":"In <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[net_v46](../../../includes/net-v46-md.md)]</ph>, randomized string hash algorithms are now supported.","pos":[98359,98468],"source":" In [!INCLUDE[net_v46](../../../includes/net-v46-md.md)], randomized string hash algorithms are now supported."},{"content":"To enable this feature, use the <ph id=\"ph1\">`aspnet:UseRandomizedStringHashAlgorithm`</ph> config setting.","pos":[98469,98558],"source":" To enable this feature, use the `aspnet:UseRandomizedStringHashAlgorithm` config setting."},{"pos":[98719,98730],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>ADO.NET<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**ADO.NET**"},{"content":"ADO .NET now supports the Always Encrypted feature available in SQL Server 2016 Community Technology Preview 2 (CTP2).","pos":[98737,98855]},{"content":"With Always Encrypted, SQL Server can perform operations on encrypted data, and best of all the encryption key resides with the application inside the customer’s trusted environment and not on the server.","pos":[98856,99060]},{"content":"Always Encrypted secures customer data so DBAs do not have access to plain text data.","pos":[99061,99146]},{"content":"Encryption and decryption of data happens transparently at the driver level, minimizing changes that have to be made to existing applications.","pos":[99147,99289]},{"content":"For details, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Always Encrypted (Database Engine)<ept id=\"p1\">](/sql/relational-databases/security/encryption/always-encrypted-database-engine)</ept> and <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>Always Encrypted (client development)<ept id=\"p2\">](/sql/relational-databases/security/encryption/always-encrypted-client-development)</ept>.","pos":[99290,99551],"source":" For details, see [Always Encrypted (Database Engine)](/sql/relational-databases/security/encryption/always-encrypted-database-engine) and [Always Encrypted (client development)](/sql/relational-databases/security/encryption/always-encrypted-client-development)."},{"pos":[99555,99595],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>64-bit JIT Compiler for managed code<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**64-bit JIT Compiler for managed code**"},{"content":"The .NET Framework 4.6 features a new version of the 64-bit JIT compiler (originally code-named RyuJIT).","pos":[99602,99706]},{"content":"The new 64-bit compiler provides significant performance improvements over the older 64-bit JIT compiler.","pos":[99707,99812]},{"content":"The new 64-bit compiler is enabled for 64-bit processes running on top of the .NET Framework 4.6.","pos":[99813,99910]},{"content":"Your app will run in a 64-bit process if it is compiled as 64-bit or AnyCPU and is running on a 64-bit operating system.","pos":[99911,100031]},{"content":"While care has been taken to make the transition to the new compiler as transparent as possible, changes in behavior are possible.","pos":[100032,100162]},{"content":"We would like to hear directly about any issues encountered when using the new JIT compiler.","pos":[100163,100255]},{"content":"Please contact us through <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Microsoft Connect<ept id=\"p1\">](https://connect.microsoft.com/)</ept> if you encounter an issue that may be related to the new 64-bit JIT compiler.","pos":[100256,100411],"source":" Please contact us through [Microsoft Connect](https://connect.microsoft.com/) if you encounter an issue that may be related to the new 64-bit JIT compiler."},{"pos":[100418,100620],"content":"The new 64-bit JIT compiler also includes hardware SIMD acceleration features when coupled with SIMD-enabled types in the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Numerics&gt;</ph> namespace, which can yield good performance improvements.","source":"The new 64-bit JIT compiler also includes hardware SIMD acceleration features when coupled with SIMD-enabled types in the <xref:System.Numerics> namespace, which can yield good performance improvements."},{"pos":[100624,100656],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Assembly loader improvements<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**Assembly loader improvements**"},{"content":"The assembly loader now uses memory more efficiently by unloading IL assemblies after a corresponding NGEN image is loaded.","pos":[100663,100786]},{"content":"This change decreases virtual memory, which is particularly beneficial for large 32-bit apps (such as Visual Studio), and also saves physical memory.","pos":[100787,100936]},{"pos":[100940,100970],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Base class library changes<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**Base class library changes**"},{"content":"Many new APIs have been added around to <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[net_v46](../../../includes/net-v46-md.md)]</ph> to enable key scenarios.","pos":[100977,101094],"source":"Many new APIs have been added around to [!INCLUDE[net_v46](../../../includes/net-v46-md.md)] to enable key scenarios."},{"content":"These include the following changes and additions:","pos":[101095,101145]},{"pos":[101153,101196],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>IReadOnlyCollection<ph id=\"ph1\">\\&lt;</ph>T&gt; implementations<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**IReadOnlyCollection\\<T> implementations**"},{"pos":[101207,101398],"content":"Additional collections implement <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Collections.Generic.IReadOnlyCollection%601&gt;</ph> such as <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.Collections.Generic.Queue%601&gt;</ph> and <ph id=\"ph3\">&lt;xref:System.Collections.Generic.Stack%601&gt;</ph>.","source":"Additional collections implement <xref:System.Collections.Generic.IReadOnlyCollection%601> such as <xref:System.Collections.Generic.Queue%601> and <xref:System.Collections.Generic.Stack%601>."},{"pos":[101406,101469],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>CultureInfo.CurrentCulture and CultureInfo.CurrentUICulture<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**CultureInfo.CurrentCulture and CultureInfo.CurrentUICulture**"},{"content":"The <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Globalization.CultureInfo.CurrentCulture%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType&gt;</ph> and <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.Globalization.CultureInfo.CurrentUICulture%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType&gt;</ph> properties are now read-write rather than read-only.","pos":[101480,101716],"source":"The <xref:System.Globalization.CultureInfo.CurrentCulture%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> and <xref:System.Globalization.CultureInfo.CurrentUICulture%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> properties are now read-write rather than read-only."},{"content":"If you assign a new <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Globalization.CultureInfo&gt;</ph> object to these properties, the current thread culture defined by the <ph id=\"ph2\">`Thread.CurrentThread.CurrentCulture`</ph> property and the current UI thread culture defined by the <ph id=\"ph3\">`Thread.CurrentThread.CurrentUICulture`</ph> properties also change.","pos":[101717,102006],"source":" If you assign a new <xref:System.Globalization.CultureInfo> object to these properties, the current thread culture defined by the `Thread.CurrentThread.CurrentCulture` property and the current UI thread culture defined by the `Thread.CurrentThread.CurrentUICulture` properties also change."},{"pos":[102014,102057],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Enhancements to garbage collection (GC)<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**Enhancements to garbage collection (GC)**"},{"pos":[102068,102279],"content":"The <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.GC&gt;</ph> class now includes <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.GC.TryStartNoGCRegion%2A&gt;</ph> and <ph id=\"ph3\">&lt;xref:System.GC.EndNoGCRegion%2A&gt;</ph> methods that allow you to disallow garbage collection during the execution of a critical path.","source":"The <xref:System.GC> class now includes <xref:System.GC.TryStartNoGCRegion%2A> and <xref:System.GC.EndNoGCRegion%2A> methods that allow you to disallow garbage collection during the execution of a critical path."},{"pos":[102290,102572],"content":"A new overload of the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.GC.Collect%28System.Int32%2CSystem.GCCollectionMode%2CSystem.Boolean%2CSystem.Boolean%29?displayProperty=nameWithType&gt;</ph> method allows you to control whether both the small object heap and the large object heap are swept and compacted or swept only.","source":"A new overload of the <xref:System.GC.Collect%28System.Int32%2CSystem.GCCollectionMode%2CSystem.Boolean%2CSystem.Boolean%29?displayProperty=nameWithType> method allows you to control whether both the small object heap and the large object heap are swept and compacted or swept only."},{"pos":[102580,102602],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>SIMD-enabled types<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**SIMD-enabled types**"},{"pos":[102613,102935],"content":"The <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Numerics&gt;</ph> namespace now includes a number of SIMD-enabled types, such as <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.Numerics.Matrix3x2&gt;</ph>, <ph id=\"ph3\">&lt;xref:System.Numerics.Matrix4x4&gt;</ph>, <ph id=\"ph4\">&lt;xref:System.Numerics.Plane&gt;</ph>, <ph id=\"ph5\">&lt;xref:System.Numerics.Quaternion&gt;</ph>, <ph id=\"ph6\">&lt;xref:System.Numerics.Vector2&gt;</ph>, <ph id=\"ph7\">&lt;xref:System.Numerics.Vector3&gt;</ph>, and <ph id=\"ph8\">&lt;xref:System.Numerics.Vector4&gt;</ph>.","source":"The <xref:System.Numerics> namespace now includes a number of SIMD-enabled types, such as <xref:System.Numerics.Matrix3x2>, <xref:System.Numerics.Matrix4x4>, <xref:System.Numerics.Plane>, <xref:System.Numerics.Quaternion>, <xref:System.Numerics.Vector2>, <xref:System.Numerics.Vector3>, and <xref:System.Numerics.Vector4>."},{"content":"Because the new 64-bit JIT compiler also includes hardware SIMD acceleration features, there are especially significant performance improvements when using the SIMD-enabled types with the new 64-bit JIT compiler.","pos":[102946,103158]},{"pos":[103166,103190],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Cryptography updates<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**Cryptography updates**"},{"content":"The <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Security.Cryptography?displayProperty=nameWithType&gt;</ph> API is being updated to support the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Windows CNG cryptography APIs<ept id=\"p1\">](/windows/desktop/SecCNG/cng-reference)</ept>.","pos":[103201,103377],"source":"The <xref:System.Security.Cryptography?displayProperty=nameWithType> API is being updated to support the [Windows CNG cryptography APIs](/windows/desktop/SecCNG/cng-reference)."},{"content":"Previous versions of the .NET Framework have relied entirely on an <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>earlier version of the Windows Cryptography APIs<ept id=\"p1\">](/windows/desktop/SecCrypto/cryptography-portal)</ept> as the basis for the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Security.Cryptography?displayProperty=nameWithType&gt;</ph> implementation.","pos":[103378,103645],"source":" Previous versions of the .NET Framework have relied entirely on an [earlier version of the Windows Cryptography APIs](/windows/desktop/SecCrypto/cryptography-portal) as the basis for the <xref:System.Security.Cryptography?displayProperty=nameWithType> implementation."},{"content":"We have had requests to support the CNG API, since it supports <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>modern cryptography algorithms<ept id=\"p1\">](/windows/desktop/SecCNG/cng-features#suite-b-support)</ept>, which are important for certain categories of apps.","pos":[103646,103848],"source":" We have had requests to support the CNG API, since it supports [modern cryptography algorithms](/windows/desktop/SecCNG/cng-features#suite-b-support), which are important for certain categories of apps."},{"content":"The .NET Framework 4.6 includes the following new enhancements to support the Windows CNG cryptography APIs:","pos":[103859,103967]},{"content":"A set of extension methods for X509 Certificates, <ph id=\"ph1\">`System.Security.Cryptography.X509Certificates.RSACertificateExtensions.GetRSAPublicKey(System.Security.Cryptography.X509Certificates.X509Certificate2)`</ph> and <ph id=\"ph2\">`System.Security.Cryptography.X509Certificates.RSACertificateExtensions.GetRSAPrivateKey(System.Security.Cryptography.X509Certificates.X509Certificate2)`</ph>, that return a CNG-based implementation rather than a CAPI-based implementation when possible.","pos":[103979,104434],"source":"A set of extension methods for X509 Certificates, `System.Security.Cryptography.X509Certificates.RSACertificateExtensions.GetRSAPublicKey(System.Security.Cryptography.X509Certificates.X509Certificate2)` and `System.Security.Cryptography.X509Certificates.RSACertificateExtensions.GetRSAPrivateKey(System.Security.Cryptography.X509Certificates.X509Certificate2)`, that return a CNG-based implementation rather than a CAPI-based implementation when possible."},{"content":"(Some smartcards, etc., still require CAPI, and the APIs handle the fallback).","pos":[104435,104513]},{"pos":[104525,104665],"content":"The <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Security.Cryptography.RSACng?displayProperty=nameWithType&gt;</ph> class, which provides a CNG implementation of the RSA algorithm.","source":"The <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.RSACng?displayProperty=nameWithType> class, which provides a CNG implementation of the RSA algorithm."},{"content":"Enhancements to the RSA API so that common actions no longer require casting.","pos":[104677,104754]},{"content":"For example, encrypting data using an <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Security.Cryptography.X509Certificates.X509Certificate2&gt;</ph> object requires code like the following in previous versions of the .NET Framework.","pos":[104755,104946],"source":" For example, encrypting data using an <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.X509Certificates.X509Certificate2> object requires code like the following in previous versions of the .NET Framework."},{"pos":[104961,105196],"content":"[!code-csharp[WhatsNew.Casting#1](~/samples/snippets/csharp/VS_Snippets_CLR/whatsnew.casting/cs/program.cs#1)]\n   [!code-vb[WhatsNew.Casting#1](~/samples/snippets/visualbasic/VS_Snippets_CLR/whatsnew.casting/vb/module1.vb#1)]","leadings":["","          "],"nodes":[]},{"content":"Code that uses the new cryptography APIs in the .NET Framework 4.6 can be rewritten as follows to avoid the cast.","pos":[105211,105324]},{"pos":[105339,105574],"content":"[!code-csharp[WhatsNew.Casting#2](~/samples/snippets/csharp/VS_Snippets_CLR/whatsnew.casting/cs/program.cs#2)]\n   [!code-vb[WhatsNew.Casting#2](~/samples/snippets/visualbasic/VS_Snippets_CLR/whatsnew.casting/vb/module1.vb#2)]","leadings":["","          "],"nodes":[]},{"pos":[105582,105645],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Support for converting dates and times to or from Unix time<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**Support for converting dates and times to or from Unix time**"},{"pos":[105656,105808],"content":"The following new methods have been added to the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.DateTimeOffset&gt;</ph> structure to support converting date and time values to or from Unix time:","source":"The following new methods have been added to the <xref:System.DateTimeOffset> structure to support converting date and time values to or from Unix time:"},{"pos":[106190,106216],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Compatibility switches<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**Compatibility switches**"},{"content":"The new <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.AppContext&gt;</ph> class adds a new compatibility feature that enables library writers to provide a uniform opt-out mechanism for new functionality for their users.","pos":[106227,106405],"source":"The new <xref:System.AppContext> class adds a new compatibility feature that enables library writers to provide a uniform opt-out mechanism for new functionality for their users."},{"content":"It establishes a loosely-coupled contract between components in order to communicate an opt-out request.","pos":[106406,106510]},{"content":"This capability is typically important when a change is made to existing functionality.","pos":[106511,106598]},{"content":"Conversely, there is already an implicit opt-in for new functionality.","pos":[106599,106669]},{"content":"With <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.AppContext&gt;</ph>, libraries define and expose compatibility switches, while code that depends on them can set those switches to affect the library behavior.","pos":[106680,106849],"source":"With <xref:System.AppContext>, libraries define and expose compatibility switches, while code that depends on them can set those switches to affect the library behavior."},{"content":"By default, libraries provide the new functionality, and they only alter it (that is, they provide the previous functionality) if the switch is set.","pos":[106850,106998]},{"content":"An application (or a library) can declare the value of a switch (which is always a <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Boolean&gt;</ph> value) that a dependent library defines.","pos":[107009,107154],"source":"An application (or a library) can declare the value of a switch (which is always a <xref:System.Boolean> value) that a dependent library defines."},{"content":"The switch is always implicitly <ph id=\"ph1\">`false`</ph>.","pos":[107155,107195],"source":" The switch is always implicitly `false`."},{"content":"Setting the switch to <ph id=\"ph1\">`true`</ph> enables it.","pos":[107196,107236],"source":" Setting the switch to `true` enables it."},{"content":"Explicitly setting the switch to <ph id=\"ph1\">`false`</ph> provides the new behavior.","pos":[107237,107304],"source":" Explicitly setting the switch to `false` provides the new behavior."},{"content":"The library must check if a consumer has declared the value of the switch and then appropriately act on it.","pos":[107420,107527]},{"content":"It's beneficial to use a consistent format for switches, since they are a formal contract exposed by a library.","pos":[108238,108349]},{"content":"The following are two obvious formats.","pos":[108350,108388]},{"pos":[108400,108433],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>Switch<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept>.<bpt id=\"p2\">*</bpt>namespace<ept id=\"p2\">*</ept>.<bpt id=\"p3\">*</bpt>switchname<ept id=\"p3\">*</ept>","source":"*Switch*.*namespace*.*switchname*"},{"pos":[108445,108476],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>Switch<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept>.<bpt id=\"p2\">*</bpt>library<ept id=\"p2\">*</ept>.<bpt id=\"p3\">*</bpt>switchname<ept id=\"p3\">*</ept>","source":"*Switch*.*library*.*switchname*"},{"pos":[108484,108540],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Changes to the task-based asynchronous pattern (TAP)<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**Changes to the task-based asynchronous pattern (TAP)**"},{"content":"For apps that target the <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[net_v46](../../../includes/net-v46-md.md)]</ph>, <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.Threading.Tasks.Task&gt;</ph> and <ph id=\"ph3\">&lt;xref:System.Threading.Tasks.Task%601&gt;</ph> objects inherit the culture and UI culture of the calling thread.","pos":[108551,108773],"source":"For apps that target the [!INCLUDE[net_v46](../../../includes/net-v46-md.md)], <xref:System.Threading.Tasks.Task> and <xref:System.Threading.Tasks.Task%601> objects inherit the culture and UI culture of the calling thread."},{"content":"The behavior of apps that target previous versions of the .NET Framework, or that do not target a specific version of the .NET Framework, is unaffected.","pos":[108774,108926]},{"content":"For more information, see the \"Culture and task-based asynchronous operations\" section of the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Globalization.CultureInfo&gt;</ph> class topic.","pos":[108927,109073],"source":" For more information, see the \"Culture and task-based asynchronous operations\" section of the <xref:System.Globalization.CultureInfo> class topic."},{"content":"The <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Threading.AsyncLocal%601?displayProperty=nameWithType&gt;</ph> class allows you to represent ambient data that is local to a given asynchronous control flow, such as an <ph id=\"ph2\">`async`</ph> method.","pos":[109084,109277],"source":"The <xref:System.Threading.AsyncLocal%601?displayProperty=nameWithType> class allows you to represent ambient data that is local to a given asynchronous control flow, such as an `async` method